A compound expression specifies a combination of other expressions. You can use any built-in function as an expression ("Function Expressions"). 
However, in a compound expression, some combinations of functions are inappropriate and are rejected.

select count(empno),ename from emp GROUP BY JOB;

select ENAME,SUM(SAL) from EMP
group by ENAME having SAL>4000;

select deptno,ename from emp group by deptno having deptno > 10;

select empno,ename,sal from emp group by deptno;

select ename,empno from emp where sal>10 order by 2;

SELECT ENAME, SUM(SAL) FROM  EMP 
GROUP BY ENAME having SAL>2000;

